00:26:37,429 --> 00:26:41,734
inside the source
of what makes us human?

516
00:26:41,822 --> 00:26:45,116
That flow, in surgery,
knowing every move

517
00:26:45,204 --> 00:26:48,057
and just feeling
how right it is...

518
00:26:48,388 --> 00:26:50,040
That's peak existence.

519
00:26:55,982 --> 00:26:58,134
I'm sorry.
I'm not gonna do the surgery.

520
00:27:05,658 --> 00:27:07,177
Are you s...

521
00:27:07,443 --> 00:27:09,950
Are you scared
to pick up a scalpel?

522
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:14,499
You had months of chemo
and radiation.

523
00:27:14,587 --> 00:27:16,214
Maybe it took its toll.

524
00:27:16,302 --> 00:27:20,082
E-Even a 10% drop in
performance would be unbearable.

525
00:27:20,170 --> 00:27:21,788
Why risk finding it out?

526
00:27:24,143 --> 00:27:25,925
Get out.

527
00:27:41,127 --> 00:27:42,474
Skydiving?

528
00:27:42,561 --> 00:27:43,643
Fugu?

529
00:27:43,730 --> 00:27:45,431
And apparently a yellow suit.

530
00:27:45,631 --> 00:27:47,299
Do you think a deadline
like he has

531
00:27:47,499 --> 00:27:49,769
burns you down
to who you really are?

532
00:27:49,969 --> 00:27:53,822
Or does it just make you
nuts and desperate?

533
00:27:54,640 --> 00:27:55,891
Why can't it be both?

534
00:27:56,108 --> 00:27:57,643
Hmm.

535
00:27:58,644 --> 00:28:00,129
Okay, um...

536
00:28:01,113 --> 00:28:03,299
A little house
in the middle of nowhere.

537
00:28:03,850 --> 00:28:05,302
Two chickens.
One dog.

538
00:28:05,450 --> 00:28:07,598
Nobody who expects
anything from me.

539
00:28:07,686 --> 00:28:09,708
Nobody who is even verbal.

540
00:28:10,957 --> 00:28:12,859
I'm tired of trying
to fix myself.

541
00:28:12,947 --> 00:28:14,583
And I'm tired of being known
as a soft touch.

542
00:28:14,670 --> 00:28:17,685
Not buying it.

543
00:28:19,778 --> 00:28:21,512
There's no way
you would get a dog

544
00:28:21,600 --> 00:28:22,770
if you only had
six months to live.

545
00:28:22,857 --> 00:28:24,441
Wouldn't be fair.

546
00:28:25,736 --> 00:28:29,774
Okay, then I would foster
a series of rescue dogs.

547
00:28:29,997 --> 00:28:32,112
You said you're tired
of being a soft touch,

548
00:28:32,200 --> 00:28:34,430
and yet your fantasy
involves helping.

549
00:28:35,447 --> 00:28:37,349
We are who we are.

550
00:29:06,012 --> 00:29:09,916
It's called stereotactic
laser ablation.

551
00:29:10,116 --> 00:29:11,600
Never liked the name.

552
00:29:24,177 --> 00:29:27,111
He said it's minimally
invasive, and if it works,

553
00:29:27,199 --> 00:29:28,716
it would save my life

554
00:29:29,020 --> 00:29:31,136
and allow me
to continue painting.

555
00:29:33,322 --> 00:29:35,153
If I win,
I win everything.

556
00:29:36,377 --> 00:29:38,112
And if I lose, it's over.

557
00:29:38,345 --> 00:29:41,245
When you first came to see Dr. Glassman,
he didn't offer this option.

558
00:29:41,333 --> 00:29:42,540
Why not?

559
00:29:43,411 --> 00:29:45,874
Stereotactic laser ablation
is a new technique,

560
00:29:45,962 --> 00:29:48,621
and it's never been used
on a Cav Mal patient.

561
00:29:48,821 --> 00:29:50,405
So, he just
didn't think of it?

562
00:29:50,493 --> 00:29:52,556
But then it came to him?

563
00:29:55,248 --> 00:29:56,819
It was my idea.

564
00:30:00,425 --> 00:30:02,975
Dr. Glassman
didn't sugarcoat the risks.

565
00:30:03,390 --> 00:30:07,280
This is the last chance
you've got to keep your art.

566
00:30:08,483 --> 00:30:11,122
I'm not going to complete
my work if I'm dead.

567
00:30:14,334 --> 00:30:15,535
No.

568
00:30:16,648 --> 00:30:18,567
But thank you so much
for trying.

569
00:30:28,758 --> 00:30:30,894
Why didn't you
back me up?

570
00:30:31,297 --> 00:30:33,747
I didn't know you were gonna
throw this crapshoot at us.

571
00:30:34,286 --> 00:30:36,093
Do you even listen
to what she's been saying?

572
00:30:36,202 --> 00:30:37,671
She wants
to finish her work.

573
00:30:37,788 --> 00:30:39,672
She could live
another 40 years,

574
00:30:39,872 --> 00:30:41,440
and her art
would grow with her.

575
00:30:41,569 --> 00:30:43,356
Don't pretend those words
mean anything to you.

576
00:30:43,442 --> 00:30:45,077
You don't give a damn
about art.

577
00:30:45,277 --> 00:30:47,020
Her family
could grow with her...

578
00:30:47,108 --> 00:30:49,811
Her children,
her grandchildren.

579
00:30:50,008 --> 00:30:53,124
You and her don't give a damn
about anything except for art.

580
00:30:54,454 --> 00:30:57,116
You need to listen to me
and do what I tell you.

581
00:30:58,860 --> 00:31:01,429
This is why
we didn't call you.

582
00:31:12,077 --> 00:31:13,387
The competition
in that family

583
00:31:13,475 --> 00:31:14,755
must have been
like a buzz saw.

584
00:31:14,944 --> 00:31:16,322
- Okay.
- Please.

585
00:31:26,418 --> 00:31:29,571
It's perfectly reasonable to
get out of a game you can't win.

586
00:31:30,022 --> 00:31:31,457
You did everything right...

587
00:31:31,545 --> 00:31:34,193
Moved 3,000 miles,
found your own calling,

588
00:31:34,281 --> 00:31:36,574
a career people respect
and value.

589
00:31:36,662 --> 00:31:39,736
Actually, there's a good comparative
measure for how people value things.

590
00:31:39,824 --> 00:31:41,010
We call it money.

591
00:31:41,098 --> 00:31:43,057
And my brother's already
a million dollars ahead.

592
00:31:43,145 --> 00:31:45,548
See how you went straight
to your brother?

593
00:31:45,972 --> 00:31:48,757
Did you ever think he might be
tired of being your competitor?

594
00:31:49,141 --> 00:31:50,542
He won a long time ago.

595
00:31:50,630 --> 00:31:52,666
That's why I left that
dysfunctional world behind.

596
00:31:52,811 --> 00:31:54,193
Really?

597
00:31:54,281 --> 00:31:57,237
Because it seems to me you re-created
the competition you grew up with

598
00:31:57,377 --> 00:31:58,834
the very first day
you got here.

599
00:32:03,656 --> 00:32:06,509
Shingles?
Like, from chicken pox?

600
