The virus was dormant,

601
00:32:08,294 --> 00:32:10,229
then your chemo suppressed
your immune system,

602
00:32:10,429 --> 00:32:11,880
and the virus woke up.

603
00:32:12,072 --> 00:32:13,532
It can be painful,

604
00:32:13,620 --> 00:32:15,369
but the treatment
is very simple.

605
00:32:17,434 --> 00:32:19,085
Do you want us
to call your wife?

606
00:32:20,596 --> 00:32:23,375
No, thank you.

607
00:32:23,575 --> 00:32:27,496
Just fix me up and
release me into the wild.

608
00:32:28,247 --> 00:32:29,898
Back to the bucket list.

609
00:32:31,483 --> 00:32:32,869
She was right.

610
00:32:34,286 --> 00:32:35,888
I'm not the same person.

611
00:32:35,976 --> 00:32:38,536
I'm doing what we all
should be doing.

612
00:32:38,624 --> 00:32:40,559
We all want to cut loose,

613
00:32:40,696 --> 00:32:42,273
but we're
just too practical.

614
00:32:42,361 --> 00:32:43,996
If this had not happened,

615
00:32:44,149 --> 00:32:48,237
I might've lived to be 90,
never looking up.

616
00:32:50,602 --> 00:32:52,330
Dr. Murphy,
what do you want to do

617
00:32:52,424 --> 00:32:54,353
that you just haven't done yet?
What makes you happy?

618
00:32:54,440 --> 00:32:56,725
I want to give Carly...
Shaun.

619
00:32:58,838 --> 00:32:59,839
Oh.

620
00:33:02,572 --> 00:33:04,491
I like a crisp apple.

621
00:33:05,534 --> 00:33:08,537
The way the sunlight
hits my bedsheets

622
00:33:08,625 --> 00:33:11,194
in the morning
in a perfect square.

623
00:33:11,521 --> 00:33:14,111
I like the movement
of wind in leaves.

624
00:33:14,873 --> 00:33:17,666
And the way the
circumference of a circle

625
00:33:17,754 --> 00:33:20,658
is always equal to pi
times the diameter,

626
00:33:20,821 --> 00:33:22,728
no matter what numbers
you put in.

627
00:33:23,931 --> 00:33:26,689
You like the happiness
of small things.

628
00:33:27,339 --> 00:33:29,221
Yes.

629
00:33:29,341 --> 00:33:31,255
Your happiness
is too loud.

630
00:33:37,015 --> 00:33:38,600
Shake your head again.

631
00:33:42,198 --> 00:33:43,467
Didn't he have
a muscle issue?

632
00:33:43,562 --> 00:33:45,197
His range of motion
seems good.

633
00:33:45,321 --> 00:33:49,627
All the better for zip-lining
in Costa Rica, right?

634
00:33:50,861 --> 00:33:52,398
Not right.

635
00:33:54,184 --> 00:33:55,955
We need more tests.

636
00:34:06,445 --> 00:34:07,830
I'm sorry.

637
00:34:09,068 --> 00:34:11,486
I know we want
the same things.

638
00:34:15,080 --> 00:34:16,664
I'd like
to show you something.

639
00:34:22,428 --> 00:34:25,313
Neurons that
fire together wire together.

640
00:34:26,598 --> 00:34:29,401
One neuron goes off,
exciting the next,

641
00:34:29,489 --> 00:34:31,358
creating a pathway
in the brain

642
00:34:31,525 --> 00:34:32,804
that wasn't
there before.

643
00:34:33,004 --> 00:34:34,907
Every time Mom
takes a brushstroke,

644
00:34:34,995 --> 00:34:36,831
every time
you use a chisel.

645
00:34:37,143 --> 00:34:40,712
It's like we're creating
ourselves in the choices we make.

646
00:34:41,041 --> 00:34:43,031
We are creating this.

647
00:34:45,016 --> 00:34:47,119
It's beautiful.

648
00:34:51,022 --> 00:34:53,137
We target
each malformation

649
00:34:53,225 --> 00:34:54,660
with a thermal laser probe.

650
00:34:54,748 --> 00:34:56,566
Just the malformation.

651
00:34:57,633 --> 00:35:00,502
The trajectory
has to be perfect.

652
00:35:01,567 --> 00:35:03,151
You can't
paint over it.

653
00:35:06,338 --> 00:35:08,189
You could show this
to Mom.

654
00:35:09,900 --> 00:35:11,618
But from you,
she'll accept it.

655
00:35:27,626 --> 00:35:30,562
Inserting the laser
probe into the cooling catheter.

656
00:35:33,799 --> 00:35:35,717
Locked and loaded.
Ready to fire.

657
00:35:37,236 --> 00:35:38,344
Dr. Glassman,

658
00:35:38,432 --> 00:35:40,172
are you sure
of this location?

659
00:35:40,372 --> 00:35:41,707
It seems significantly far

660
00:35:41,795 --> 00:35:43,847
from what we saw
on her pre-surgical MRIs.

661
00:35:45,444 --> 00:35:49,148
You know what the brain and
breakfast cereal have in common?

662
00:35:49,236 --> 00:35:51,921
Contents tend to shift
during transport.

663
00:35:53,719 --> 00:35:55,403
Yes, I'm quite sure.

664
00:36:06,365 --> 00:36:08,072
First ablation complete.

665
00:36:18,720 --> 00:36:22,106
Now we just have to do it
perfectly nine more times.

666
00:36:31,814 --> 00:36:33,037
It's gone?

667
00:36:33,124 --> 00:36:34,826
Well, not quite.
But close.

668
00:36:34,914 --> 00:36:36,590
The recent infections
got into the tumor.

669
00:36:36,678 --> 00:36:39,814
Which allowed your
immune system to find it.

670
00:36:40,060 --> 00:36:43,531
But they said it was
an aggressive cancer.

671
00:36:43,669 --> 00:36:45,062
What makes
a cancer aggressive

672
00:36:45,150 --> 00:36:47,706
